'''Jude Laspa''' is an American former [[vice president]] and [[director]] of the [[Bechtel|Bechtel Group]].<ref name=ccst>{{cite web|url= http://www.ccst.us/ccstinfo/council/bios/laspa.php|title=Jude Laspa|publisher=[[California Council on Science and Technology]]|accessdate=October 7, 2013}}</ref>

==Biography==
Laspa obtained his bachelor's degree in [[engineering]] from the [[Harvey Mudd College]] and later got his [[Master of Business Administration]] degree from the [[University of Chicago]]. He was in charge of both the [[Exploratorium]] and the ''Rainbird Corporation''. By 2010, he retired as Vice-Chair of the [[Board of Trustees]] of his alma mater and the same year was retired from Bechtel where he served for 43 years. His career there ranged from being a sponsor of [[fellow]]s to being President of one its divisions, called ''Bechtel Systems and Infrastructure''. He even was a [[chairman]] of ''BGI Group Strategy Committee'', and served as both a manager and senior vice-president of the company's fossil-power business.<ref name=ccst/>

